Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the pasta. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @Echalion Shallot{1}. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Roughly chop the @Olives{30}. Halve the @Baby Plum Tomatoes{125} and roughly chop the @Flat Leaf Parsley{1}(chopped) (stalks and all). Place the tomatoes and parsley in a #bowl{} and season with a pinch of @salt{pinch}.

Add the @Rigatoni Pasta{180%g} to your boiling water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}. Once cooked, drain the pasta in a #colander{} and pop back into the pan. Drizzle with @olive oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a large #frying pan{} on medium heat and add the @Pine Nuts{15%g} (no oil). Toast them until golden, ~{2-3%minutes}, tossing regularly. When golden, transfer them from your pan to a small bowl.

> Watch pine nuts like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Pop your (now empty) frying pan back on medium heat and add a drizzle of @?olive oil{}. Add the shallot to your pan, then stir and cook until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add the garlic and @Tomato Puree{30%g}, stir and cook for ~{1%minute} more. Pour in the @Chopped Tomatoes{1}(finely chopped), olives and @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%g}. Add a pinch of @?sugar{pinch} (if you have some). Bring to a simmer and cook until reduced by half, ~{10%minutes}.

While your sauce cooks, finely chop the @Chives{1}(finely chopped). Drain the @Mozzarella{1} and pull it apart into small pieces. Stir the @Balsamic Vinegar{12%g}, @Honey{15%g} and @Olive Oil{for the Dressing} for the dressing into the bowl of tomatoes.

> If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

When your sauce is cooked, season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}, then add the cooked pasta and toss together. Stir through half the chives and half the torn mozzarella pieces. Share the pasta into #bowls{}, then spoon tomato salsa on top. Finish with the remaining mozzarella, chives and a sprinkle of pine nuts. Enjoy!

> Mod Step: If you've decided to add bacon to your meal, add @?British Smoked Bacon Lardons{90%g} to the pan when you add the shallot and cook until the shallot has softened and the bacon is crispy, 4-5 mins. Add the garlic and tomato puree and continue with the step and the recipe.